Q1. Python program to calculate the product and sum of all the elements of the list. 
SOLUTION:
lst=[10,20,30,40,50]
index=0
product=1
sum=0
while index<len(lst):
    product=product*lst[index]
    sum=sum+lst[index]
    index=index+1
print("List =",lst)
print("Total Product =",product)
print("Total sum =",sum)

Q2. Python program to check if the given number is Prime or not. 
SOLUTION:
num=int(input("Enter the number"))
i=2
f=0
while i<num:
    if num%i==0:
        f=1
        break
    i=i+1    
if f==1:
    print("Not prime")
else:
    print("prime") 

Q3. program to take an input of 10 numbers and print its average using while loop. 
SOLUTION:
i=1
sum=0
while i<=10:
    print("Enter the value #",1)
    n=int(input("Enter the value"))
    sum=sum+n
    avg=sum/10
    i=i+1
print("Average of numbers =",avg)

